# Collaborative Whiteboard Selection System

## Background
Liveblocks is a real-time collaboration infrastructure. In this task, you will build a React application with a whiteboard where multiple users can see who has selected which shape in real-time.

## Requirements
- Create a React application (e.g., using Vite) with `@liveblocks/client` and `@liveblocks/react`.
- Implement a whiteboard canvas with at least three selectable shapes.
- Users can click a shape to select it. Only one shape can be selected by a user at a time.
- Clicking the whiteboard background (outside of any shape) clears the user's selection.
- The selection state must be synchronized across clients in real-time using Liveblocks `Presence`.
- The application must visually indicate which shape is selected by the current user and which shapes are selected by other users.
- The Liveblocks room name must be `whiteboard-room-${run-id}` to avoid conflicts across test runs.

## Implementation Hints
- Use `createClient` with the `LIVEBLOCKS_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable.
- Define `Presence` in your Liveblocks configuration to include a `selectedShape` property (e.g., storing the shape ID).
- Use `useMyPresence` to update the current user's selection when they click a shape or the background.
- Use `useOthers` to retrieve the presence of other users and determine if a shape is selected by someone else.
- Read the `run-id` from the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable and use it to construct the room name passed to `RoomProvider`.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Project path: `/home/user/whiteboard-app`
- Start command: `npm run dev -- --port 5173 --host`
- Port: `5173`
- UI Elements:
  - A whiteboard container element with `id="whiteboard"`.
  - At least three shape elements inside the whiteboard, each with a unique `data-shape-id` attribute (e.g., `"shape-1"`, `"shape-2"`, `"shape-3"`).
  - When the current user selects a shape, that shape element must have a `data-selected-by-me="true"` attribute.
  - When another user selects a shape, that shape element must have a `data-selected-by-others="true"` attribute.
  - When a shape is not selected by the current user, it should not have `data-selected-by-me="true"`.
  - When a shape is not selected by any other user, it should not have `data-selected-by-others="true"`.


