# Liveblocks Comment Sidebar with Resolve Feature

## Background
Liveblocks provides a complete Comments API for building threaded discussions. In this task, you will build a React application with a comment sidebar that allows users to create threads and mark them as "Resolved" using custom metadata.

## Requirements
- Create a React application with Liveblocks configured.
- Implement a comment sidebar UI that displays a list of threads.
- Users must be able to create new threads.
- Users must be able to mark a thread as "Resolved". This should be implemented by updating a custom `metadata` field (e.g., `resolved: true`) on the thread.
- Resolved threads should visually indicate their resolved status (e.g., displaying "Resolved" text) or be hidden from the default view.
- The app must connect to a unique room using the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable.

## Implementation Hints
- Use `@liveblocks/client`, `@liveblocks/react`, and `@liveblocks/react-ui`.
- Configure `LiveblocksProvider` with the `LIVEBLOCKS_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable.
- Wrap your app in a `RoomProvider` with the room ID set to `room-${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ZEALT_RUN_ID || process.env.ZEALT_RUN_ID}`.
- Configure your `liveblocks.config.ts` (or equivalent) to include custom metadata types for threads (e.g., `ThreadMetadata` with a `resolved` boolean).
- Use `useThreads` to fetch and display threads.
- Use `useCreateThread` to allow users to create new threads.
- Use `useEditThreadMetadata` to update the `resolved` status of a thread when a "Resolve" button is clicked.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Project path: /home/user/liveblocks-app
- Start command: npm run dev
- Port: 3000
- The app must connect to the Liveblocks room `room-${run-id}` where `${run-id}` is the value of the `ZEALT_RUN_ID` environment variable.
- The UI must have a way to create a new thread with an initial message.
- Each thread in the UI must have a "Resolve" button (or similar control) that updates the thread's metadata to set `resolved: true`.
- The UI must visually indicate resolved threads or filter them out.


